---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Case Studies | Blog
breadcrumbTitle: Case Studies
description: Browse Musifer case studies for applied breakdowns, process notes, and proof-oriented reading as that lane grows.
---
{% set bucket = blog.publicBucketMap["case-studies"] %}

<div class="l-page-shell l-module-stack blog-bucket-page">
  <section class="card card-impact blog-bucket-header" aria-labelledby="case-studies-heading">
    <p class="blog-kicker">Blog / Case studies</p>
    <h1 class="card-title display-title" id="case-studies-heading">{{ bucket.title }}</h1>
    <p class="blog-page-deck">{{ bucket.hubDescription }}</p>
  </section>

  <section class="card" aria-labelledby="case-studies-list-heading">
    <div class="blog-section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="blog-kicker">Current publishing</p>
        <h2 class="card-title" id="case-studies-list-heading">What is live in this lane</h2>
        <p class="blog-section-copy">{{ bucket.countLabel }}</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn--secondary" href="/blog/">Back to blog hub</a>
    </div>

    {% if bucket.entries.length %}
    <div class="module-card-stack">
      {% for entry in bucket.entries %}
      <article class="blog-bucket-entry">
        <p class="blog-inline-meta">{{ entry.metadataLabel }}</p>
        <h3 class="card-title">{{ entry.title }}</h3>
        <p>{{ entry.summary }}</p>
        <a class="blog-inline-link" href="{{ entry.url }}">Read case study</a>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="blog-empty-state">
      <p>Case studies are part of the public structure now, but they are being held until there is enough real material to justify the lane.</p>
      <div class="blog-browse-links">
        <a class="btn" href="/blog/">Return to the blog hub</a>
        <a class="btn btn--secondary" href="/services/rates-quote/">Use the quote path</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </section>
</div>
